WEBVTT

00:00:04.839 --> 00:00:10.136
Is the destiny of mankind controlled
by some transcendental entity or Law?

00:00:10.928 --> 00:00:13.931
Is it like the hand of
God hovering above?

00:00:14.932 --> 00:00:16.892
At least it is true...

00:00:17.268 --> 00:00:20.896
...that man has no
control, even over his own will.

00:00:24.734 --> 00:00:29.030
I don't want live like
this, buried in his dream...

00:00:33.034 --> 00:00:34.076
You and Griffith...

00:00:36.078 --> 00:00:40.332
I hope you and
Griffith work out together...

00:00:42.835 --> 00:00:43.711
Hey.

00:00:46.464 --> 00:00:48.674
Judeau, Corkus...

00:00:53.721 --> 00:00:55.431
Give us your company for a moment.

00:01:05.524 --> 00:01:06.525
Griffith!

00:01:07.026 --> 00:01:09.070
He would be able to stop him!

00:01:31.801 --> 00:01:33.719
<i>Feel no shame about shape.</i>

00:01:33.969 --> 00:01:35.721
<i>Weather changes the phrase.</i>

00:01:35.930 --> 00:01:39.433
<i>Even mother will
show you another way.</i>

00:01:39.725 --> 00:01:41.852
<i>So, put your glasses on.</i>

00:01:41.977 --> 00:01:43.938
<i>Nothing will be wrong.</i>

00:01:44.063 --> 00:01:46.107
<i>There's no blame, there's no fame.</i>

00:01:46.357 --> 00:01:47.983
<i>It's up to you.</i>

00:01:48.192 --> 00:01:51.612
<i>The first words should be found.</i>

00:01:52.321 --> 00:01:55.241
<i>Whatever holds you back.</i>

00:01:55.991 --> 00:01:56.617
<i>I...</i>

00:01:56.992 --> 00:01:57.743
<i>... can...</i>

00:01:57.868 --> 00:01:59.954
<i>I can get it off.</i>

00:02:00.079 --> 00:02:00.996
<i>Tell me what...</i>

00:02:01.122 --> 00:02:01.956
<i>Tell me what...</i>

00:02:02.081 --> 00:02:03.749
<i>Tell me what you want.</i>

00:02:03.958 --> 00:02:04.875
<i>I don't know why...</i>

00:02:05.126 --> 00:02:05.876
<i>I don't know why...</i>

00:02:06.001 --> 00:02:07.878
<i>I don't know why you are afraid.</i>

00:02:08.129 --> 00:02:09.004
<i>Tell me what...</i>

00:02:09.171 --> 00:02:09.922
<i>Tell me what...</i>

00:02:10.172 --> 00:02:11.632
<i>Tell me what you'd say.</i>

00:02:11.924 --> 00:02:12.925
<i>I don't know why...</i>

00:02:13.134 --> 00:02:14.051
<i>I don't know why...</i>

00:02:14.176 --> 00:02:14.802
<i>Too late...</i>

00:02:15.010 --> 00:02:16.512
<i>It's too late.</i>

00:02:21.642 --> 00:02:25.646
Separation

00:02:31.652 --> 00:02:33.821
What is this all of a sudden?

00:02:33.946 --> 00:02:34.280
<i>Come here, girl!</i>

00:02:34.280 --> 00:02:35.072
It's not sudden.
<i>Come here, girl!</i>

00:02:35.072 --> 00:02:35.447
<i>Come here, girl!</i>

00:02:36.073 --> 00:02:38.534
I've was thinking about this
before we set off for our last battle.

00:02:38.909 --> 00:02:39.577
<i>Hey darling, when do you...</i>

00:02:39.577 --> 00:02:41.287
Are you discontent about something?
<i>Hey darling, when do you...</i>

00:02:41.287 --> 00:02:42.329
Of course not, not at all.

00:02:42.329 --> 00:02:43.330
Of course not, not at all.
<i>... get off work?</i>

00:02:43.330 --> 00:02:44.039
<i>But...</i>

00:02:44.165 --> 00:02:44.832
<i>Why don't you spend...</i>

00:02:44.832 --> 00:02:46.167
During these past three years...
<i>Why don 't you spend...</i>

00:02:46.333 --> 00:02:46.667
<i>... some time with me later?</i>

00:02:46.667 --> 00:02:47.960
...I've been having fun.
<i>... some time with me later?</i>

00:02:47.960 --> 00:02:48.460
<i>... some time with me later?</i>

00:02:48.711 --> 00:02:50.588
It's been like some kind of festival.

00:02:50.713 --> 00:02:51.338
<i>I don't know...</i>

00:02:51.338 --> 00:02:51.964
How could I be discontent?
<i>I don't know...</i>

00:02:51.964 --> 00:02:52.715
How could I be discontent?

00:02:53.048 --> 00:02:53.340
<i>Oh, I didn't ask your name yet...</i>

00:02:53.340 --> 00:02:54.675
Then, why do you...
<i>Oh, I didn't ask your name yet...</i>

00:02:54.675 --> 00:02:55.092
<i>Oh, I didn't ask your name yet...</i>

00:02:55.426 --> 00:02:57.219
Corkus, come on.

00:02:57.344 --> 00:02:57.970
Shut up!

00:02:58.429 --> 00:03:01.182
I am Sir Corkus, commander of
an entire company of the Hawks!

00:03:01.432 --> 00:03:05.311
What's wrong with me going to
a bar and making a play for a girl or two?

00:03:07.229 --> 00:03:09.565
We've got free reign
in any bar in Windam...

00:03:09.732 --> 00:03:12.985
...once they recognize us
as the Hawks' commanders!

00:03:13.194 --> 00:03:16.614
In the street, we're mobbed
by kids and women as we walk by!

00:03:16.822 --> 00:03:18.199
Of course!

00:03:18.324 --> 00:03:20.868
We are the heroes
who saved this kingdom!

00:03:21.076 --> 00:03:23.871
Soon, we'll be
admitted into society as nobles!

00:03:24.079 --> 00:03:26.332
We'll be able to
settle down in the Court!

00:03:26.457 --> 00:03:28.751
With luck, we could
become landed lords!

00:03:29.210 --> 00:03:32.254
All of this would be impossible
under ordinary circumstances!

00:03:32.379 --> 00:03:33.130
Right?

00:03:33.505 --> 00:03:36.759
But, we finally obtained it!

00:03:36.884 --> 00:03:39.136
And we sweated blood over it!

00:03:39.637 --> 00:03:43.349
Nonetheless, you will give up all this...

00:03:45.476 --> 00:03:46.393
In any case...

00:03:46.518 --> 00:03:49.897
It's no wonder you can't
dance with the ladies at a party.

00:03:50.022 --> 00:03:53.484
You're not capable of
doing anything but slay men!

00:03:54.401 --> 00:03:56.028
What you say is true.

00:03:56.904 --> 00:04:00.908
I can't do anything but wield a sword.

00:04:05.996 --> 00:04:11.168
When I first killed a man, I was just a
kid without any idea what I was doing.

00:04:11.919 --> 00:04:15.381
I have not known
anything more than battle...

00:04:15.547 --> 00:04:17.091
I never tried to know more...

00:04:17.758 --> 00:04:19.385
To survive, I kill...

00:04:19.510 --> 00:04:21.136
...that's all I've ever done.

00:04:21.512 --> 00:04:22.221
But...

00:04:22.721 --> 00:04:24.640
I could have lived with that...

00:04:25.224 --> 00:04:26.225
If only...

00:04:26.892 --> 00:04:27.851
If one person...

00:04:28.352 --> 00:04:30.521
If anyone had looked my way...

00:04:33.649 --> 00:04:34.650
However...

00:04:35.734 --> 00:04:38.737
...I learned my lesson as I
wandered from battle to battle...

00:04:39.029 --> 00:04:43.117
I learned that wishes wouldn't help
me crush the skulls of my enemies.

00:04:43.993 --> 00:04:46.036
My complaints were just childish.

00:04:46.745 --> 00:04:48.122
But I also realized...

00:04:49.164 --> 00:04:50.791
...that I had met someone...

00:04:50.916 --> 00:04:53.168
...from whom I
really wanted attention...

00:04:57.756 --> 00:05:00.551
He had nothing
whatsoever in his possession.

00:05:01.302 --> 00:05:03.804
And he intended to obtain everything.

00:05:06.181 --> 00:05:10.060
However, because he
aspires to reach such great heights...

00:05:10.269 --> 00:05:14.440
...he is forced to be on
edge almost constantly.

00:05:14.898 --> 00:05:20.154
That's why he cannot afford
to let the weak get close to him.

00:05:21.280 --> 00:05:24.575
I feel strange saying
this, but when I look at him...

00:05:24.700 --> 00:05:27.036
...it's like looking up into a bright light.

00:05:29.955 --> 00:05:36.086
I can't deal with it any more, admiring
him and being caught up in his dream...

00:05:38.172 --> 00:05:42.968
I want to be an equal with him, I want to
have something I can achieve by myself.

00:05:43.302 --> 00:05:47.848
I don't want him to be the
only thing holding me back.

00:05:48.349 --> 00:05:51.060
You said you want to
be equal with Griffith?

00:05:52.811 --> 00:05:54.188
Cut the crap!

00:05:54.313 --> 00:05:56.065
You're bitching like some rotten kid!

00:05:56.482 --> 00:05:57.983
He <i>is</i> special!

00:05:58.192 --> 00:05:59.693
He is different from us!

00:05:59.860 --> 00:06:02.237
It's thanks to no one
but Griffith that someone...

00:06:02.363 --> 00:06:05.366
...good for nothing but slaying men, can
be Commander of the Hawks' Raiders!

00:06:05.616 --> 00:06:07.993
You're already surpassing your limits!

00:06:08.202 --> 00:06:11.080
I'm not interested in
that position or rank at all.

00:06:11.372 --> 00:06:13.499
What I really want to
have is something different...

00:06:13.874 --> 00:06:16.126
Something more,
something I have to win by myself!

00:06:16.627 --> 00:06:18.837
You're talking
nonsense, like some stupid kid!

00:06:19.004 --> 00:06:21.256
Something you
have to win by yourself?

00:06:21.840 --> 00:06:25.010
No one would suffer if that
kind of thing was easy to find!

00:06:25.219 --> 00:06:26.011
Listen!

00:06:26.136 --> 00:06:30.391
A man has to make many compromises
in his life, because of his personal limits...

00:06:30.516 --> 00:06:32.768
...and his
responsibility to face up to reality.

00:06:33.602 --> 00:06:35.896
Only a child can be
content with just a dream.

00:06:36.021 --> 00:06:37.731
Don't give me your crap!

00:06:37.773 --> 00:06:42.027
Your words are nothing but excuses
for a coward who can't face reality!

00:06:42.736 --> 00:06:43.654
Corkus...

00:06:45.280 --> 00:06:46.407
You...

00:06:47.157 --> 00:06:49.743
Don't you have anything like that?

00:06:52.496 --> 00:06:53.664
Gimme a break!

00:06:54.039 --> 00:06:55.666
I need to get some sleep!

00:06:55.916 --> 00:06:58.419
I can't tolerate this
immature fool any longer!

00:07:01.046 --> 00:07:07.177
Despite all that, he used to be
great leader in an organization of thieves.

00:07:08.512 --> 00:07:13.058
I suppose he must have once had
something he wanted to win by himself...

00:07:13.183 --> 00:07:15.060
...even if it was only a small thing.

00:07:17.187 --> 00:07:18.313
As for myself...

00:07:18.439 --> 00:07:21.817
...I have rather cleverly managed every
feat of skill I've tried since I was a kid.

00:07:24.319 --> 00:07:29.074
I was more skilled with a sword or a
dagger than others, and more tactful as well.

00:07:30.909 --> 00:07:34.288
But I could never be a
master at any one thing.

00:07:34.788 --> 00:07:37.958
I decided to follow someone who
did have the potential to be a master...

00:07:38.041 --> 00:07:40.961
...so I wouldn't have to be
signaled out as the special one.

00:07:42.212 --> 00:07:45.215
I think everyone has the
desire to gain something...

00:07:48.469 --> 00:07:50.179
I'll see you out...

00:07:50.471 --> 00:07:54.349
I hope you can find
something you really want.

00:08:00.564 --> 00:08:01.690
Hey, Guts...

00:08:01.815 --> 00:08:02.441
Yeah?

00:08:02.566 --> 00:08:05.110
How about you and Caska?

00:08:05.235 --> 00:08:05.736
What?

00:08:06.195 --> 00:08:07.488
What was that?

00:08:07.988 --> 00:08:11.116
She likes Griffith,
everybody knows that.

00:08:11.992 --> 00:08:15.120
I don't think Caska can
get together with Griffith.

00:08:15.245 --> 00:08:15.996
Why?

00:08:16.371 --> 00:08:19.708
There's one thing that Griffith pursues.

00:08:20.626 --> 00:08:25.255
Getting princess Charlotte is a
shortcut on the path to fulfill Griffith's dream.

00:08:25.589 --> 00:08:27.633
That's the best thing for him to do.

00:08:28.634 --> 00:08:32.137
Anyway, what do you think of Caska?

00:08:33.555 --> 00:08:36.183
Caska is an attractive woman.

00:08:36.934 --> 00:08:40.646
It's unusual to find a woman
who is reliable on the battlefield.

00:08:41.813 --> 00:08:45.317
But I consider her
only as my comrade...

00:08:46.443 --> 00:08:47.569
...not as a woman.

00:08:47.694 --> 00:08:48.403
So...

00:08:54.910 --> 00:08:55.577
No...

00:08:56.703 --> 00:08:57.829
...it's not possible.

00:08:58.664 --> 00:09:01.792
She looks at only Griffith.

00:09:02.584 --> 00:09:05.671
So for now, I'm not
able to be her match.

00:09:08.048 --> 00:09:09.091
I see.

00:09:10.092 --> 00:09:13.595
I guess I was the only one who
thought there was some hope for you.

00:09:18.934 --> 00:09:21.311
Thanks for coming along, I'm off now...

00:09:27.484 --> 00:09:28.443
Guts!

00:09:28.986 --> 00:09:29.736
You...

00:09:29.861 --> 00:09:32.614
You're so mean, how could
you leave without saying anything?

00:09:33.198 --> 00:09:34.116
Why?

00:09:34.241 --> 00:09:36.118
Are you tired of the Hawks?

00:09:36.243 --> 00:09:37.327
Ricket...

00:09:49.256 --> 00:09:50.507
Are you leaving?

00:09:50.841 --> 00:09:51.717
Yeah...

00:09:52.593 --> 00:09:54.886
Are you resigning from
the Band of the Hawk?

00:09:56.096 --> 00:09:57.139
Sorry...

00:09:58.599 --> 00:10:00.517
We don't understand your apology!

00:10:00.642 --> 00:10:02.019
Please tell us why!

00:10:02.227 --> 00:10:05.272
Aren't the Hawks
supposed to be a family?

00:10:05.772 --> 00:10:07.274
Stop it, Ricket.

00:10:07.399 --> 00:10:08.150
Why...

00:10:08.358 --> 00:10:10.110
It's a man's decision.

00:10:10.402 --> 00:10:12.112
We should just let him go.

00:10:12.237 --> 00:10:15.157
But Guts is the
Commander of the Hawks' Raiders.

00:10:15.282 --> 00:10:17.242
He is key to the Hawks!

00:10:18.285 --> 00:10:21.163
We were already
invincible before he joined.

00:10:21.371 --> 00:10:21.997
But...

00:10:22.122 --> 00:10:22.914
Shut up!

00:10:25.417 --> 00:10:27.794
Hey, I'm going to tell you this now!

00:10:28.170 --> 00:10:30.297
I have hated you so much!

00:10:30.672 --> 00:10:32.299
I will never admit it...

00:10:32.674 --> 00:10:34.801
You are not special!

00:10:35.302 --> 00:10:38.055
You will never be like Griffith!

00:10:40.807 --> 00:10:43.018
If we meet on the battlefield sometime...

00:10:43.310 --> 00:10:45.187
...you had better watch your back!

00:10:49.900 --> 00:10:50.901
Guts...

00:10:53.320 --> 00:10:54.946
Thanks for everything...

00:11:20.097 --> 00:11:22.099
I told you this long ago...

00:11:22.474 --> 00:11:24.601
You are mine.

00:11:35.445 --> 00:11:37.864
I won you by my sword.

00:11:38.740 --> 00:11:42.744
Everything about you belongs to me,
from your battlefield to your own life.

00:11:43.620 --> 00:11:46.206
If you want to get free of my hand...

00:11:46.581 --> 00:11:47.999
...by those conditions...

00:11:48.500 --> 00:11:50.252
Snatch yourself free with your blade!

00:11:50.752 --> 00:11:51.837
Griffith!

00:11:52.212 --> 00:11:55.257
Couldn't you just let me go
by saying good-bye with smile?

00:11:59.010 --> 00:11:59.970
I see.

00:12:07.519 --> 00:12:08.395
Hold it!

00:12:09.396 --> 00:12:10.897
Are you two serious?

00:12:11.273 --> 00:12:13.400
Are comrades willing to kill each other?

00:12:17.154 --> 00:12:18.655
Stay back, Caska!

00:12:20.031 --> 00:12:21.491
Don't get in our way!

00:12:21.658 --> 00:12:22.784
What are you saying?

00:12:22.909 --> 00:12:25.662
If you two fight with real swords,
you won't escape unharmed!

00:12:27.289 --> 00:12:28.999
Hands off, what are you doing?

00:12:29.166 --> 00:12:31.752
There's no way around it,
in these circumstances...

00:12:33.420 --> 00:12:34.921
What are you all doing?

00:12:35.130 --> 00:12:36.631
We've got to stop
them, they'll kill each other.

00:12:36.923 --> 00:12:38.550
This is their concern, not yours.

00:12:38.759 --> 00:12:40.886
We don't have to interrupt this.

00:12:42.179 --> 00:12:43.305
But we can't just...

00:12:43.430 --> 00:12:46.308
Have you become so much
of a lady that you've forgotten?

00:12:47.017 --> 00:12:49.519
We have to settle
things by our swords.

00:12:49.686 --> 00:12:51.688
This is our way as mercenaries, isn't it?

00:12:52.522 --> 00:12:53.440
But...

00:12:54.691 --> 00:12:56.401
She has changed...

00:12:56.443 --> 00:12:59.196
She never hesitated
before under Griffith's orders...

00:12:59.321 --> 00:13:02.032
...even if her comrades
were in mortal danger.

00:13:02.699 --> 00:13:06.077
Is she herself aware
of how she's changed?

00:13:12.209 --> 00:13:14.461
His eyes look as if
he's glaring at an enemy.

00:13:15.796 --> 00:13:16.588
But...

00:13:17.297 --> 00:13:21.176
...even if he hates me or
if he considers me a traitor...

00:13:23.220 --> 00:13:24.721
I've got to go!

00:13:28.975 --> 00:13:31.228
It's just as it was three years ago...

00:13:31.937 --> 00:13:35.190
I've ended up fighting with my sword
just as I started fighting with my sword.

00:13:35.607 --> 00:13:37.609
Well, that's just the way I like it.

00:13:38.568 --> 00:13:41.988
The duel tells me that you
at least value me enough...

00:13:42.614 --> 00:13:44.366
...to fight and bleed over me.

00:13:45.992 --> 00:13:48.995
He has become immensely strong...

00:13:49.371 --> 00:13:50.247
But...

00:13:50.997 --> 00:13:53.834
Griffith can definitely stop him!

00:13:54.501 --> 00:13:58.713
Then, everything will be
the same as it was before...

00:14:01.132 --> 00:14:02.592
Is that my wish?

00:14:03.009 --> 00:14:04.636
Is it my wish that...

00:14:06.471 --> 00:14:08.598
...Guts stays with us?

00:14:14.646 --> 00:14:17.107
He makes no attempt
to display his will to fight.

00:14:18.024 --> 00:14:19.901
However, he is completely on guard...

00:14:21.152 --> 00:14:22.863
...his eyes are free of confusion.

00:14:25.782 --> 00:14:27.659
Do you really desire to be...

00:14:28.660 --> 00:14:30.287
...free of my hand so much?

00:14:30.912 --> 00:14:32.622
No, I won't allow it!

00:14:33.915 --> 00:14:35.917
My best chance is in the first strike...

00:14:36.167 --> 00:14:38.920
I've got to deflect his sword as
soon as he swings downward.

00:14:39.045 --> 00:14:40.672
Then I'll strike his shoulder!

00:14:41.423 --> 00:14:45.427
What if I kill him as a result of
my sword striking off the mark?

00:14:46.261 --> 00:14:50.682
I don't care, not if
he refuses to be mine...

00:14:51.016 --> 00:14:51.808
I care not!

00:15:07.574 --> 00:15:08.283
Now!

00:15:38.730 --> 00:15:39.731
Griffith!

00:15:51.242 --> 00:15:52.077
Bye...

00:15:59.709 --> 00:16:00.961
Griffith...

00:16:23.108 --> 00:16:25.151
Guts!

00:16:37.622 --> 00:16:41.292
Guts is gone, he didn't even look back.

00:16:41.543 --> 00:16:42.377
That was a fluke!

00:16:42.502 --> 00:16:44.045
That was definitely a fluke!

00:16:44.295 --> 00:16:45.755
I'll never admit that he won!

00:16:50.927 --> 00:16:52.303
You're going to be all right...

00:16:53.054 --> 00:16:55.932
You just stumbled
over a stone in the street...

00:16:56.683 --> 00:16:58.435
It's not a big deal at all...

00:17:00.812 --> 00:17:04.065
Your goal is far
beyond things like this, right?

00:17:05.025 --> 00:17:07.277
I'm sure you'll overcome this.

00:17:08.153 --> 00:17:11.156
You'll start walking again soon...

00:17:26.171 --> 00:17:27.922
No, the snow is melting...

00:17:28.506 --> 00:17:32.802
Please go to bed quickly,
otherwise you will get sick, My lady.

00:17:33.136 --> 00:17:34.179
I will go to bed.

00:17:34.304 --> 00:17:35.930
You may leave now.

00:17:36.181 --> 00:17:37.932
Then, good night My Lady.

00:17:55.075 --> 00:17:56.409
Sir Griffith!

00:17:58.078 --> 00:18:00.455
Sir Griffith, what happened to you?

00:18:00.830 --> 00:18:02.707
It's such a rainy night!

00:18:03.041 --> 00:18:05.335
Good evening, Princess Charlotte.

00:18:05.794 --> 00:18:08.797
Would you mind if I asked for
admittance into your chamber?

00:18:09.047 --> 00:18:09.839
What?

00:18:10.090 --> 00:18:14.094
If someone saw us like this,
it might stain your honor, Princess.

00:18:14.677 --> 00:18:15.970
Y-Yes...

00:18:17.472 --> 00:18:18.556
Come in...

00:18:18.598 --> 00:18:19.432
Thank you.

00:18:20.600 --> 00:18:23.812
Please excuse my rudeness,
visiting a lady's chamber...

00:18:24.729 --> 00:18:27.357
...so late at night, and making it wet.

00:18:30.610 --> 00:18:32.487
I missed you so much.

00:18:33.238 --> 00:18:35.490
Ever since you were
sent to the battlefield...

00:18:35.573 --> 00:18:39.077
...I have constantly been afraid
that I would hear of your death.

00:18:39.577 --> 00:18:43.248
After you came back, fearful and sorrowful
things have occurred one after another.

00:18:44.124 --> 00:18:48.878
Why, why didn't you
come to see me earlier?

00:19:00.140 --> 00:19:01.015
No...

00:19:11.901 --> 00:19:13.236
Griffith...

00:19:15.655 --> 00:19:16.906
Griffith!

00:19:18.283 --> 00:19:19.784
Are you scared?

00:19:23.371 --> 00:19:24.289
Stop it...

00:19:24.914 --> 00:19:31.045
Your fear and sorrow, throw
everything into a fire, and let it burn...

00:20:40.990 --> 00:20:41.866
Bye...

00:21:00.134 --> 00:21:01.511
Griffith?

00:21:18.903 --> 00:21:23.533
Well, well, who should it be but Your
Excellency, the next White Hawk General!

00:21:24.409 --> 00:21:28.037
To think that Your Excellency, of
all people, should be here at this time.

00:21:30.039 --> 00:21:31.916
That's right, my sword was...

00:21:32.667 --> 00:21:35.795
I will hear your
story later, at my leisure.

00:21:36.379 --> 00:21:37.255
Haul him off!

00:22:03.031 --> 00:22:05.158
<i>Looking back, the morning comes.</i>

00:22:05.199 --> 00:22:08.786
<i>Don't find your face in your glass.</i>

00:22:10.038 --> 00:22:12.832
<i>Take the moonlight by the tail.</i>

00:22:12.957 --> 00:22:15.793
<i>It's a rainy sight that you're shading.</i>

00:22:17.545 --> 00:22:19.047
<i>What is that?</i>

00:22:19.172 --> 00:22:20.340
<i>It's just the same.</i>

00:22:20.465 --> 00:22:23.468
<i>What is trying on your crown?</i>

00:22:24.719 --> 00:22:27.680
<i>I'm spending my
glass and walking back.</i>

00:22:27.805 --> 00:22:30.975
<i>So wear my glass, you're fading.</i>

00:22:31.351 --> 00:22:34.604
<i>I'm waiting so long.</i>

00:22:35.063 --> 00:22:37.982
<i>I'm waiting so long.</i>

00:22:38.691 --> 00:22:41.736
<i>I'm waiting so long.</i>

00:22:42.612 --> 00:22:45.365
<i>I'm waiting...</i>

00:23:06.886 --> 00:23:08.888
Next Episode

00:23:10.348 --> 00:23:14.352
A friend who has been left,
a place that has been lost...

00:23:14.602 --> 00:23:16.521
...a feeling that has been abandoned...

00:23:16.771 --> 00:23:19.732
It is fate's mischief
bringing such things about.

00:23:20.274 --> 00:23:24.153
Even when a man has joy, there is
torment lurking on the other side of it.

00:23:24.987 --> 00:23:30.743
Why does blissful time
always fly away in a twinkling?

00:23:33.913 --> 00:23:36.916
Sparks

00:23:37.305 --> 00:24:37.292
